./"Simple Shell manual page
.TH Simple_Shell "2022-12-08" "Simple Shell man page" Simple_Shell

.SH NAME
Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
[options] [command_string | file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Simple Shell is an sh-compatible command language interpreter that
executes commands read from the standard input or from a file.

Simple shell is a final semester project which is basicly an interface between the user and the kernel,
it is a linux command lines interpreter as simple as this.

.SH COMMAND

ls: Shows the contents of a folder.

mkdir: Create a folder.

rmdir: Delete a folder

touch: create a file.

rm: Delete files

cp: copy a file to another place.

mv: Move a file.

cat: Shows the contents of a file.

echo: displays what you write.

pwd: Shows the path of the folder where we are.

sleep: "Sleep" system during the seconds you indicate.

sh, bash: Interpreters of commands.

chmod: Change the permissions of a file.

chgrp: Change a file group.

chown: Change the user of a file.

.SH EXAMPLE OF THE COMMAND

Suppose that the following command is entered by keyboard: ls -a, The result when executing the command will be the all files in directory you choose.

.SH AUTHOR
Wael Abidi (https://github.com/weedii)
